The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the 15th anniversary of the President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR) at the White House. Pence praised the work of faith-based organizations in combating HIV/AIDS and announced that the administration will invest $100 million in new resources to expand engagement with these organizations. He also highlighted the progress made in the fight against HIV/AIDS, including the decrease in new infections and the success of PEPFAR in saving lives and preventing the spread of the disease. Pence emphasized the administration's commitment to ending the AIDS crisis and thanked the bipartisan support in Congress for reauthorizing PEPFAR.